.Dd July 5, 2026
.Dt FIGPUT 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm figput ,
.Nm put_config ,
.Nm set_config_option
.Nd configuration file modification library
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libfigput
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In figput.h
.Ft int
.Fo put_config
.Fa "struct figput_config options[]"
.Fa "const char *path"
.Fa "uint16_t processing_options"
.Fa "uint16_t put_options"
.Fc
.Ft int
.Fo set_config_option
.Fa "struct figput_config options[]"
.Fa "const char *directive"
.Fa "union figput_cfgvalue *value"
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
library provides a light-weight,
portable framework for modifying configuration files.
It is the write-side complement to
.Xr figpar 3 :
where that library reads directives and values,
.Nm
edits them in place,
adds directives that are absent,
and removes directives that are no longer wanted,
while preserving comments,
blank lines,
statement ordering,
and the formatting of untouched statements.
.Pp
Configuration directives,
types,
actions,
and results are described by an array of data structures defined in
.In figput.h :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
struct figput_config {
    enum figput_cfgtype		type;		/* value type */
    const char			*directive;	/* keyword */
    union figput_cfgvalue	value;		/* value to write */
    uint8_t			action;		/* action to perform */
    uint16_t			result;		/* NB: set by put_config */
    uint32_t			line;		/* NB: set by put_config */

    /* Reserved for a future custom serialiser; leave NULL */
    int (*write)(struct figput_config *option);
};
.Ed
.Pp
The array is terminated by an entry whose
.Va directive
member is
.Dv NULL .
.Pp
When a value is written,
it is always taken from the
.Va value.str
member as a null-terminated string,
regardless of
.Va type ;
the type governs only whether the value is quoted on output.
Callers therefore stringify numeric and boolean values themselves,
which keeps the on-disk spelling entirely under the caller's control.
.Pp
The
.Va action
member of each option selects one of:
.Bl -tag -width FIGPUT_ACTION_SET_VALUE
.It Dv FIGPUT_ACTION_SET_VALUE
Set the directive to
.Va value.str ,
editing it in place if it already exists or appending it to the file if it does
not.
This is the default
.Pq zero
action.
.It Dv FIGPUT_ACTION_CHECK
Report,
via
.Va result ,
whether the current value differs from
.Va value ,
without modifying the file.
.It Dv FIGPUT_ACTION_REMOVE
Delete the directive from the file.
.El
.Pp
On return,
the
.Va result
member of each processed option is set to a mask of:
.Bl -tag -width FIGPUT_DIRECTIVE_REMOVED
.It Dv FIGPUT_DIRECTIVE_FOUND
The directive was present in the file.
.It Dv FIGPUT_VALUE_CHANGED
The value was
.Pq or would be, for Dv FIGPUT_ACTION_CHECK
changed.
.It Dv FIGPUT_DIRECTIVE_ADDED
The directive was absent and has been appended.
.It Dv FIGPUT_DIRECTIVE_REMOVED
The directive was present and has been removed.
.El
.Pp
The
.Va line
member is set to the line number of the first match,
or zero if the directive was not found.
.Pp
The
.Fa processing_options
argument to
.Fn put_config
is a mask of bit fields controlling how the file is tokenised.
These flags have exactly the meaning documented for the corresponding
.Dv FIGPAR_*
flags in
.Xr figpar 3 ,
and must match those used to parse the same file:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width FIGPUT_BREAK_ON_SEMICOLON -compact
.It Dv FIGPUT_BREAK_ON_EQUALS
.It Dv FIGPUT_BREAK_ON_SEMICOLON
.It Dv FIGPUT_CASE_SENSITIVE
.It Dv FIGPUT_REQUIRE_EQUALS
.It Dv FIGPUT_STRICT_EQUALS
.El
.Pp
Unlike
.Xr figpar 3 ,
directives are matched exactly rather than with
.Xr fnmatch 3 ,
since a glob pattern is not a writable target.
.Pp
The
.Fa put_options
argument is a mask of bit fields controlling how output is written:
.Bl -tag -width FIGPUT_NO_SAVE_DUPLICATES
.It Dv FIGPUT_NO_SAVE_DEFAULTS
Do not rewrite a directive whose new value is identical to the value already
present in the file.
.It Dv FIGPUT_NO_SAVE_DUPLICATES
Abort with an error if a directive being modified appears more than once in the
file.
.It Dv FIGPUT_SAVE_ALLOW_EMPTY
Permit a
.Dv FIGPUT_ACTION_SET_VALUE
option to carry an empty value.
Without this flag,
an empty value for any type other than
.Dv FIGPUT_TYPE_NONE
is an error.
.It Dv FIGPUT_SAVE_BACKUP
Before replacing the original,
copy it to a file with the same name plus a
.Ql .bak
suffix.
.It Dv FIGPUT_SAVE_UNQUOTED
Write string values verbatim,
without adding surrounding quotes or escapes.
.El
.Pp
.Fn put_config
replaces the file atomically.
Output is written to a temporary file created in the same directory as
.Fa path ,
flushed to stable storage with
.Xr fsync 2 ,
given the mode
.Pq and, where permitted, the ownership
of the original,
and then
.Xr rename 2 Ap d
over it.
If any error occurs the original file is left untouched and the temporary file
is removed.
.Pp
.Fn set_config_option
traverses the options array and,
for the first option whose
.Fa directive
matches via
.Xr strcmp 3 ,
stages
.Fa value
into that option's
.Va value
member.
It returns 1 on success,
or 0 if no matching directive was found or an argument was
.Dv NULL .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Rv -std put_config
.Sh ERRORS
In addition to the errors documented for
.Xr open 2 ,
.Xr read 2 ,
.Xr write 2 ,
.Xr fstat 2 ,
.Xr mkstemp 3 ,
.Xr realpath 3 ,
and
.Xr rename 2 ,
.Fn put_config
may fail if:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EINVAL
The
.Fa options
or
.Fa path
argument was
.Dv NULL ,
.Fa path
did not resolve to a regular file,
or a
.Dv FIGPUT_ACTION_SET_VALUE
option carried an empty value without
.Dv FIGPUT_SAVE_ALLOW_EMPTY .
.It Bq Er EEXIST
.Dv FIGPUT_NO_SAVE_DUPLICATES
was set and a modified directive appeared more than once.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr figpar 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
library first appeared in
.Fx 16.0 .
